{"metadata":{"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"MLNOverlay","kind":"identifier"}],"externalID":"c:objc(pl)MLNOverlay","modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"symbolKind":"protocol","title":"MLNOverlay","roleHeading":"Protocol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNOverlay"}]},"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre"]]},"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"topicSections":[{"title":"Instance Properties","anchor":"Instance-Properties","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/coordinate","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/overlayBounds"]},{"title":"Instance Methods","anchor":"Instance-Methods","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/intersectsOverlayBounds:"]}],"relationshipsSections":[{"type":"inheritsFrom","kind":"relationships","title":"Inherits From","identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation"]},{"type":"conformingTypes","kind":"relationships","title":"Conforming Types","identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolygon","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolyline","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPointCollection","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolyline"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"@protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MLNOverlay","kind":"identifier"},{"text":" <","kind":"text"},{"text":"MLNAnnotation","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","preciseIdentifier":"c:objc(pl)MLNAnnotation","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":">","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["occ"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"overview","text":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You use overlays to layer more sophisticated content on top of a map view. For","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"example, you could use an overlay to show the boundaries of a national park or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"trace a bus route along city streets. This SDK defines several concrete classes","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that conform to this protocol and define standard shapes.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay"]}],"abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" protocol defines a specific type of annotation that represents","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"both a point and an area on a map. Overlay objects are essentially data objects","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that contain the geographic data needed to represent the map area. Overlays can","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"take the form of a polyline or polygon.","type":"text"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay","interfaceLanguage":"occ"},"references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","abstract":[{"text":"Powerful, free and open-source mapping toolkit with full control over data sources and styling.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","title":"MapLibre","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre","role":"collection"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNMultiPolyline":{"title":"MLNMultiPolyline","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNMultiPolyline"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnmultipolyline","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolyline","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" object represents a shape consisting of one or more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"polylines. For example, you could use a multipolyline shape to represent both"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"sides of a divided highway (dual carriageway), excluding the median (central"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reservation): each carriageway would be a distinct "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolyline","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" object."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolyline"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNPointCollection":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPointCollection","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpointcollection","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"An ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPointCollection","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" object represents a shape consisting of one or more","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"disconnected vertices, specified as ","type":"text"},{"code":"CLLocationCoordinate2D","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instances. The","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"points in the collection may be related but are not connected spatially. For","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"example, you could use a point collection to represent all the trees in an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"orchard.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"text":"MLNPointCollection","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","title":"MLNPointCollection","kind":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNPolygon":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" object represents a closed shape consisting of four or more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"vertices, specified as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CLLocationCoordinate2D"},{"type":"text","text":" instances, and the edges that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"connect them. For example, you could use a polygon shape to represent a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"building, a lake, or an area you want to highlight."}],"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpolygon","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNPolygon"}],"title":"MLNPolygon"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNMultiPolygon":{"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnmultipolygon","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolygon","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" object represents a shape consisting of one or more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"polygons that do not overlap. For example, you could use a multipolygon shape"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to represent the body of land that consists of an island surrounded by an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"atoll: the inner island would be one "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" object, while the surrounding"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"atoll would be another. You could also use a multipolygon shape to represent a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"group of disconnected but related buildings.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNMultiPolygon"}],"role":"symbol","title":"MLNMultiPolygon","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolygon","kind":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotation":{"title":"MLNAnnotation","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotation","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","fragments":[{"text":"MLNAnnotation","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" protocol is used to provide annotation-related information","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to a map view. To use this protocol, you adopt it in any custom objects that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"store or represent annotation data. Each object then serves as the source of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"information about a single map annotation and provides critical information,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"such as the annotation’s location on the map. Annotation objects do not provide","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the visual representation of the annotation but typically coordinate (in","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"conjunction with the map view’s delegate) the creation of an appropriate","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"objects to handle the display.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNPolyline":{"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpolyline","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNPolyline"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolyline","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" object represents a shape consisting of two or more vertices,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"specified as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CLLocationCoordinate2D"},{"type":"text","text":" instances, and the line segments that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"connect them. For example, you could use an polyline to represent a road or the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"path along which something moves."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolyline","title":"MLNPolyline","role":"symbol","type":"topic","kind":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay/overlayBounds":{"type":"topic","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay\/overlaybounds","title":"overlayBounds","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The cooordinate rectangle that encompasses the overlay. (required) (read-only)"}],"fragments":[{"text":"overlayBounds","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/overlayBounds","kind":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay/intersectsOverlayBounds:":{"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Returns a Boolean indicating whether the specified rectangle intersects the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"receiver’s shape.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"text","text":"- "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"intersectsOverlayBounds:"}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay\/intersectsoverlaybounds:","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"intersectsOverlayBounds:"}],"title":"intersectsOverlayBounds:","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/intersectsOverlayBounds:","type":"topic"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay/coordinate":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/coordinate","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay\/coordinate","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A coordinate representing the overlay. (required) (read-only)"}],"title":"coordinate","fragments":[{"text":"coordinate","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","type":"topic","kind":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNOverlay"}],"type":"topic","title":"MLNOverlay","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol defines a specific type of annotation that represents"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"both a point and an area on a map. Overlay objects are essentially data objects"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that contain the geographic data needed to represent the map area. Overlays can"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"take the form of a polyline or polygon."}]}}}